🔸Direkte Sonneneinstrahlung auf der Haut ist wichtig für die körpereigene Produktion von Vitamin D3 - diese kann für eine gewisse Zeit von Körper gespeichert werden
🔹In der Regel ist es uns kaum möglich in unseren Breitengraden den Bedarf an Vitamin D durch Sonneneinstrahlung zu decken, wodurch wir vor allem in den Wintermonaten einen ständigen Mangel haben, weswegen eine zusätzliche Einnahme dessen durchaus empfehlenswert wäre 😊👏🏼 #tipps #health #vitamin #vitamind3 #body #supplements #energy

I cannot express how happy I am to have earned my 10 mile Run For Your Life medal from @hogwartsrunningclub 
It's really hard to believe that at one point I couldn't walk a mile without being exhausted. And here I am jogging/walking ten miles at once! 
I am thrilled and amazed at how far I have come! Between my workouts and finding #hogwartsrunningclub I am improving more and more each day! 
I used to shy away from jogging outside, afraid people would judge me, but I finally realized that their opinion doesn't matter. Because I AM ENOUGH! 🏃🏻‍♀️☺️

#transformationtuesday! 4 years between pics.
-
Time will play the biggest role in the overall look of your muscles. Muscle maturity is one of the most overlooked things when it comes to results. Also the lighting was really good here and that makes a BIG difference! I was surprised to see any lines in my back because I rarely train it much anymore. It's always been a strong area so I tend to just do a few rowing motions each week and it maintains well. It looks bigger in the picture than it looks in person lol! -
I know many will want to know the weight between pictures, and I really don't know. The first picture was at my first NPC bikini competition and I was somewhere around 105 to 110 pounds. Now I'd say I'm closer to 125-ish. But again I rarely weigh myself so I don't really know. The last time I weighed myself I was 127. The weight that I'm at now is easily maintainable for me. I'm healthy, I feel good and I'm not hungry LOL hallelujah!

First pic was when I turned 12....the right pic I took a couple days ago. It wasn't easy to get where I'm at right know, I worked my ass off and I'm gonna keeping working till I reach my goals. A good work ethic, a good mindset can take you far. There are no shortcuts or secret supplement or pill that will help you reach that goal body. You have to be consistent and put in the work that's all it takes. We're just getting started, can't wait to see where I'm at in the future💪🏻
